{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI"],"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" documentation provides the matching API reference for the modifiers described here.","type":"text"}]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping"],"title":"Explanation","generated":true,"anchor":"Explanation"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The bundled UI is intentionally opinionated. Each modifier picks the platform-appropriate presentation so consumers don’t have to repeat the conditional compilation themselves, and so the dispatch flow stays symmetric across platforms — the same ","type":"text"},{"code":".paywall(.dismiss)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" action fires from a ","type":"text"},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on iOS and from a sheet on macOS.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article explains the reasoning behind those choices and what is fixed versus configurable."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"revenueCatPaywall","text":"revenueCatPaywall","level":2},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reason"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}]}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A subscription paywall is a primary moment, not an interrupt. ","type":"text"},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keeps the UI immersive, prevents accidental gesture-dismiss, and matches App Store conventions.","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"frame(minWidth: 400, minHeight: 600)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mac sheets do not expand to fill the parent window. Without an explicit minimum size the paywall would render too small to legibly show plan options. The 400×600 minimum is roughly the size RevenueCatUI’s templates assume."}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because neither presentation offers a system dismissal affordance ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":" has no swipe-to-dismiss; Mac sheets have no default close control), the modifiers show "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":"’s close button by default. Pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"displayCloseButton: false"},{"type":"text","text":" only for a hard paywall the user must purchase through — and make sure some other path out of that screen exists."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The minimum frame is hard-coded; it is not exposed as a parameter. If your paywall layout needs more room on macOS, wrap the modified view in a parent that imposes a larger frame, or use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" directly inside a custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","anchor":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reason","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RevenueCatUI ships a customer center on iOS only. A non-fullscreen "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" is appropriate because customer-center actions are administrative, not part of a purchase flow."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Opens "},{"code":"itms-apps:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and immediately fires "},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS, and the system has no equivalent in-app surface. The App Store subscription management page is what users expect on the Mac, so the sheet hands off to it and clears its own presentation state immediately.","type":"text"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The macOS branch clears the binding and fires ","type":"text"},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" synchronously after ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSWorkspace.shared.open","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState.isCustomerCenterPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" does not get stuck ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The user returns from App Store to find the app’s UI in its idle state. If nothing on the system handles the ","type":"text"},{"code":"itms-apps","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" scheme, the hand-off falls back to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions"},{"type":"text","text":" web URL in the default browser."}]},{"level":2,"text":"One surface at a time","anchor":"One-surface-at-a-time","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The composed "},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall(state:offeringIdentifier:displayCloseButton:send:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier never asks the platform to present the paywall and the customer center simultaneously — UIKit refuses a second presentation from the same host, which would leave the refused surface’s state flag stuck "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with nothing on screen. The paywall wins: while "},{"code":"PaywallState.isPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" the customer-center binding reads "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and a request for either surface while the other is up dispatches "},{"code":".dismissCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" so state and screen stay in agreement."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apps wiring the primitive modifiers manually own this rule themselves; keep the two presentation flags mutually exclusive.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Why no platform-override hooks","anchor":"Why-no-platform-override-hooks","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both modifiers are deliberately parameter-light: an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPresented: Binding<Bool>"},{"type":"text","text":", an optional "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss: () -> Void"},{"type":"text","text":", and — on the paywall only — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"displayCloseButton:"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offeringIdentifier:"},{"type":"text","text":". There is no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"paywallStyle:"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"presentationKind:"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reasoning: any consumer that needs to deviate from the chosen presentation already has the underlying RevenueCatUI types ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":") and SwiftUI’s full presentation surface ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"popover"},{"type":"text","text":", custom containers). The bundled modifiers exist to handle the 95% case in one line — when the 5% case applies, drop down to RevenueCatUI directly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This package does not try to be the complete paywall-UI library. It is the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"integration layer","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" that makes the common case trivial.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"What is configurable","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"What-is-configurable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The configurable surface lives in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI"},{"type":"text","text":" and on the paywall plugin:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywall content, copy, and template"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" renders whichever offering and template the dashboard returns."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Customer-center labels, sections, and actions"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" renders whichever configuration the dashboard returns.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Close button","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"displayCloseButton:"},{"type":"text","text":" on the paywall modifiers. Defaults to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"; pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" for a hard paywall."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Presentation triggering"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — driven by the plugin via "},{"code":"PaywallState.isPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"isCustomerCenterPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Your code chooses "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"when"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to set them via "},{"code":".request(reason:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":".presentCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" actions."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Dismiss behavior"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — dismiss actions are dispatched by the presentation bindings themselves (","type":"text"},{"code":".dismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the paywall, ","type":"text"},{"code":".dismissCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the customer center). The primitive modifiers’ ","type":"text"},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" callbacks are purely additive — use them for analytics hooks or cleanup, not for dispatch.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Offering selection"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offeringIdentifier:"},{"type":"text","text":" on the paywall modifiers presents a specific RevenueCat offering (a win-back or regional offer, for example). Omit it for the dashboard’s current offering. An unknown identifier or a failed fetch falls back to the current offering with a logged warning, so a stale identifier degrades gracefully instead of dead-ending the purchase flow."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Why the ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifiers present differently on iOS and macOS, and what is hard-coded.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/platformbehavior"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Platform Behavior","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}]},"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/EntitlementMapping":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/entitlementmapping","title":"Entitlement Mapping","abstract":[{"text":"How RevenueCat’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"CustomerInfo.entitlements","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to Swidux’s "},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"article"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"abstract":[{"text":"Attach the ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" view modifiers from ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to a root view, driven by ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"title":"How to Present the UI","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":". Implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" against "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with "},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for drop-in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"text":" presentation.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection"}}}